Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Halve,
peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @bell
pepper{1}. Mince @parsley{¼%ounce} leaves and stems. Remove @Italian pork sausage{9%ounce} from casings; discard casings.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add onion, bell pepper, and half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Add sausage and another drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} to #pan. Cook,
breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
~{5-7%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking
water, then drain.

Once sausage is cooked through, add @diced tomatoes{14%ounce} to pan. Season
with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and remaining Tuscan Heat Spice. Bring to a boil,
then lower heat and let simmer while spaghetti cooks. After you've drained
spaghetti, stir @chicken stock concentrate{1} and ¾ cup reserved pasta
cooking water into pan. Continue simmering until slightly reduced,
~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add spaghetti to #pan; toss to coat. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon},
half the parsley, and half the @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup}. Season with salt and
pepper. Divide between bowls and sprinkle with remaining parsley and Parmesan.

> If pasta seems dry, add more reserved pasta cooking water as needed.